claim.claim-text:
1. A method for processing a datastream, comprising the steps of:
identifying a first data unit having channel information conveyed within ancillary information included in the datastream;
identifying a plurality of second data units included in the first data unit and related to selection of a program represented by packets of compressed digital data representing video and audio information, each said plurality of second data units having a fixed length whereby each of said plurality of second data units are separated from other second data units by a multiple of a fixed offset, whereby a desired one of the second data units can be located from the plurality of second data units utilizing said fixed offset;
determining services associated with the program and respective packet identifiers associated with the services in response to the plurality of second data units; and
utilizing said packet identifiers to identify and acquire data packets associated with the program from the datastream.

6. A method for processing a datastream, comprising the steps of:
identifying a first data unit having channel information conveyed within ancillary information included in the datastream, the first data unit comprising a second data unit having information related to additional program information data units included in the datastream, and a third data unit;
identifying a plurality of fourth data units included in the third data unit and related to selection of a program represented by packets of compressed digital data representing video and audio information, each said plurality of fourth data units having a fixed length;
identifying a first one of the fourth data units in the first data unit, and identifying a second one of the fourth data units, which follows the first one of the fourth data units in the datastream, utilizing an offset from the first one of the fourth data unit, the offset being a multiple of the fixed length;
determining services associated with the program and respective packet identifiers associated with the services in response to the plurality of fourth data units; and
utilizing said packet identifiers to identify and acquire data packets associated with the program from the datastream.
